# Version bump (required)

NexVUE ships a semver file at repo root `VERSION` (shown in the top-nav via
`nexvue-version.php`). **Update it in the same change set** whenever you finish
userful work — do not leave VERSION stale.

## When to bump

- **Patch (x.y.Z):** bug fixes, copy/docs-only that operators rely on, small UI
  polish, test-only fixes tied to behavior.
- **Minor (x.Y.0):** new features, new ops actions, new Settings/Services
  controls, player behavior changes, new deploy helpers.
- **Major (X.0.0):** breaking config/API/pipeline changes operators must notice.

Skip bump only for pure chore with zero user/operator impact (e.g. typo in an
agent transcript, formatting that cannot affect runtime).

## How

1. Read `VERSION`, choose the next semver, write the single-line file
   (`1.2.3` — no `v` prefix, no extra text).
2. Keep README/CLAUDE mentions of versioning accurate if you touch those docs.
3. Do not invent git tags unless the user asks; bumping `VERSION` is enough for
   the UI badge after `setup.sh` / Update from repo.

## Example

```text
# was 1.0.0 — added Services → Update from repo
1.1.0
```
